e** in the project. No Go files currently use `import \"embed\"`.\n\n## Files to Embed\n\nThe `.devcontainer` directory at `/workspaces/vscode-dashboard/.devcontainer/` contains:\n\n```\n/workspaces/vscode-dashboard/.devcontainer/\n├── devcontainer.json\n├── dot-config.json\n├── setup-agents.sh\n├── setup-bash.sh\n└── setup.sh\n```\n\n## Current devcontainer.go Package\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/vscode-dashboard/wt/pkg/devcontainer/devcontainer.go`\n\nThe package currently has three functions:\n1. `HasDevcontainer(path string) bool` - Checks if .devcontainer folder exists\n2. `GetPrimaryDevcontainerPath(path string) (string, error)` - Gets .devcontainer path from primary project\n3. `CreateDevcontainer(path string) error` - Scaffold function (not yet implemented)\n\n## File I/O Patterns in the Codebase\n\nThe existing codebase uses the standard library approach for file operations:\n\n**Pattern from `/workspaces/vscode-dashboard/wt/pkg/config/config.go`:**\n```go\n// Reading files\ndata, err := os.ReadFile(configPath)\n\n// Writing files  \nif err := os.WriteFile(configPath, data, 0644); err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to write config file: %w\", err)\n}\n\n// Creating directories\nif err := os.MkdirAll(configDir, 0755); err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create config directory: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern from `/workspaces/vscode-dashboard/wt/pkg/workspace/workspace.go`:**\n```go\n// Reading files\ndata, err := os.ReadFile(srcPath)\n\n// Writing files\nif err := os.WriteFile(dstPath, data, 0644); err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to write workspace file: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n## Key Insights for Embedding\n\n1. **Go Version:** Go 1.25.6 fully supports `embed` package\n2. **Current Pattern:** Uses `os.ReadFile()` and `os.WriteFile()` for file operations\n3. **Path Structure:** Embedded files need to be in a path relative to the package location\n4. **No Existing Examples:** You'll be the first to use `embed` in this project, so you can establish the pattern\n5. **Module Name:** `github.com/bmingles/wt` - use this as reference for import paths\n\nTo embed files from `.devcontainer/` into the `wt/pkg/devcontainer` package, you would typically:\n- Place the files in a relative path from the package directory\n- Use `//go:embed` directives with file paths relative to the package\n- Store the embedded data in `embed.FS` or byte variables\n- Serve files via `fs.FS` interface when needed"}],"totalDurationMs":20170,"totalTokens":30206,"totalToolUseCount":15,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":517,"cache_read_input_tokens":28452,"output_tokens":1230,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":517,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
